full_text:
@ChrisB1574 @dudanlang new translators

it's tough working with translation here, so i think it's wise to explain to people interested working in this field how things *actually* work
full_text(utf-8): b"@ChrisB1574 @dudanlang new translators\n\nit's tough working with translation here, so i think it's wise to explain to people interested working in this field how things *actually* work"

b'@ChrisB1574 @dudanlang only public/sworn translators are allowed to translate documents and such
they usually get most of the clients (and work), so they often "hire" people to help them

we are allowed to look for our own clients, but having direct clients is a bit unusual, especially for +'

full_text: @aidanstudies which books are you using? there's a few ones like ciao a tutti that have a lot of text that are suitable for your level... articles may be a bit of a though read at a1/a2 level

full_text:
@ChrisB1574 @dudanlang so it's a bit difficult to make your breakthrough as a translator
also the government doesn't properly recognize us, so even stuff like paying our taxes is a nightmare
full_text(utf-8): b"@ChrisB1574 @dudanlang so it's a bit difficult to make your breakthrough as a translator\nalso the government doesn't properly recognize us, so even stuff like paying our taxes is a nightmare"

b"@ChrisB1574 @dudanlang i work with english, italian and portuguese \xf0\x9f\x98\x8a
although im currently working under a public translator, so i have someone to correct my work

but here in brazil almost 70% of job offers are EN-PT and, as there's a lot of translators, a lot of the are charging really low prices"

b"@ChrisB1574 @dudanlang well, im just saying how things are right now in brazil in the translation business... it's a tough career path \xf0\x9f\x98\x85\ni'm a translator myself and i usually have to work during WE and holidays (if i want to make any money at all)\n+ you can't choose the right client if you have none"

full_text:
@dudanlang not really having any clients (or money lol) for at least 2-3 years when you're trying to establish your career, studying a lot, researching A LOT, having to deal with projects/topics youre not really interested about or know about

@smart_polyglot @el_explorador_ i think what bothers me most is people messing up the concepts of language acquisition vs language learning (in literally every discussion lol)
 
in linguistics acquisition refers only to our mother language, that is, we acquire only our native language, not foreign ones
